<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1887-03-22T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1887-03-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="55" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d55">
                    <head>No. 55.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Bayard</persName>
                            to Mr. <persName type="to">Trail</persName></hi>.</head>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1887-03-22"><hi rend="italic">March</hi> 22,
                            1887</date>.</dateline>
                        <seg rendition="#left">No. 53.]</seg></opener>
                    <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have your No. 73 of the 22d ultimo,
                        communicating a note of the chief of police, to our consul at Santos,
                        regretting the occurrence there on the 9th January, during which a supposed
                        attack with stones was made on the consulate. The matter seems to be
                        disposed of satisfactorily.</p>
                    <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                    <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">T. F. Bayard.</hi></signed></closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>